### Money Tracker API - HTTP Requests

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api/v1
@contentType = application/json

### ============================================
### USER ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Create a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Walter Onyango",
  "email": "walter.developer@tech.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Get user profile with all wallets and overall balance
# /users/{userId}
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/019c9086-436e-70c2-9b74-a80340ce8484
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### ============================================
### WALLET ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Create a new wallet for a user
POST {{baseUrl}}/wallets
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "user_id": "019c9086-436e-70c2-9b74-a80340ce8484",
  "name": "Personal Account"
}

### Get wallet details with balance and all transactions
# /wallets/{walletId}
GET {{baseUrl}}/wallets/019c9088-045e-7021-841f-55f2f538044c
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### Update wallet name
PUT {{baseUrl}}/wallets/019c9088-045e-7021-841f-55f2f538044c
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Updated Business Account"
}

### Delete a wallet
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/wallets/019c908b-678a-7224-817e-0903d22a2058
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### ============================================
### TRANSACTION ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Create income transaction
POST {{baseUrl}}/wallets/019c9088-045e-7021-841f-55f2f538044c/transactions
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "type": "income",
  "amount": 5000.50,
  "description": "Monthly salary",
  "date": "2026-02-24"
}

### Create expense transaction
POST {{baseUrl}}/wallets/019c9088-045e-7021-841f-55f2f538044c/transactions
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "type": "expense",
  "amount": 250.75,
  "description": "Office supplies",
  "date": "2026-02-24"
}

### Get all transactions for a wallet
GET {{baseUrl}}/wallets/019c9088-045e-7021-841f-55f2f538044c/transactions
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### Get a specific transaction
# /transactions/{transactionId}
GET {{baseUrl}}/transactions/019c908e-7e03-738a-ba93-c2a709d85c2d
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
